'''K-Lite Codec Pack''' is a collection of [[Audio file format|audio]] and [[video]] components for [[Microsoft Windows]] that enables the [[operating system]] and its [[software]] to play back various audio and video formats generally not supported by the operating system itself. K-Lite Codec Pack also includes several related tools, including [[Media Player Classic]], [[GSpot|GSpot Codec Information Appliance]], and Codec Tweak Tool.<ref name="codecguide-about">{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/about_kl.htm |title=About the K-Lite Codec Pack |publisher=[http://www.codecguide.com The official website â CodecGuide.com] |accessdate=18 October 2009}}</ref>

==Details==
===Editions===
There are five editions of K-Lite Codec Pack, all being available free of charge.<ref name="codecguide-about" />
# '''Basic:''' The Basic edition is the smallest version and enables a Microsoft Windows computer to play [[Matroska|Matroska (MKV)]], [[MP4]], [[Ogg]] and [[Flash Video|Adobe Flash video (FLV)]] files, in addition to various types of [[Audio Video Interleave|AVI]] files. It only consists of [[ffdshow]] (for audio and video decoding), [[DirectVobSub]] (for subtitle decoding), Codec Tweak Tool and four other minor components. This edition does not come with [[Media Player Classic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/features_basic.htm |title=Contents of K-Lite Codec Pack Basic |publisher=The official website â CodecGuide.com |accessdate=18 October 2009}}</ref>
# '''Standard:''' The Standard edition includes all features of the Basic edition plus a [[DVD Video]] decoder, Media Info Lite and [[Media_Player_Classic#Media_Player_Classic_Home_Cinema|Media Player Classic Home Cinema]]. This edition enables DVD playback in Microsoft Windows.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/features_standard.htm |title=Contents of K-Lite Codec Pack Standard |publisher=The official website â CodecGuide.com |accessdate=18 October 2009}}</ref> This package is recommended for normal users.<ref name="codecguide-about" />
# '''Full:''' The Full edition includes 31 additional components and four additional tools beyond those included in the Standard edition, as well as adding video encoding capabilities to Microsoft Windows PCs. However, no encoding or conversion tool is included in the package.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/features_full.htm |title=Contents of K-Lite Codec Pack Full |publisher=The official website â CodecGuide.com |accessdate=18 October 2009}}</ref>
# '''Mega:''' The ''K-Lite Mega Codec Pack'' is a combination of ''K-Lite Codec Pack Full'', [[Real Alternative]], and fourteen additional components not present in any other edition. Amongst these components, there is the original Media Player Classic as well as Media Player Classic Home Cinema, [[GSpot|GSpot Codec Information Appliance]], and FourCC Changer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/features_mega.htm |title=Contents of K-Lite Mega Codec Pack |publisher=The official website â CodecGuide.com |accessdate=18 October 2009}}</ref>
# '''64-bit:''' The [[64-bit]] K-Lite Codec Pack is an independent package of codecs that can be used with 64-bit players on a 64-bit version of Microsoft Windows. This edition can co-exist with one of the other editions, and in fact the developers recommend installing the 64-bit pack after installing one of the regular packs.<ref name="x64-edition">{{cite web |url=http://codecguide.com/klcp_64bit.htm |title=K-Lite Codec Pack 64-bit |accessdate=26 July 2011|publisher=codecguide.com}}</ref>

